                    <comment id="12918125" author="osm" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 20:24:44 +0100"  >This patch is for 4.0.3-RELEASE&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Provides an exposed method for convenience when having to encode redirected URIs.</comment>
                    <comment id="12918130" author="olegk" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 20:32:08 +0100"  >Ryan,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please have a look at HttpClient 4.1-alpha2 release or SVN trunk. The DefaultRedirectStrategy class in 4.1 has a very similar method &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
protected URI createLocationURI(final String location) throws ProtocolException;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I can commit the patch but it is very unlikely there will be another official release off the 4.0.x branch. Please consider upgrading to 4.1.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Oleg </comment>
